post_text:
The Millville Area Elementary School will continue with Technology distribution to all students in grades 3 through 6 on Monday, August 24th from 1 p.m. to 6 p.m. and Tuesday, August 25th from 8 a.m. to 6 p.m. through the Elementary Office entrance. You may need these devices to participate in your virtual open house/meet the teacher presentations that will be posted in your Sapphire Community Portal. Please practice social distancing and wear face coverings when picking up your devices. If you can’t come during these times, please call the Elementary School office.
You should receive a link via your Sapphire Community Portal and/or an email from your teacher for your scheduled meeting. Meeting times are also posted on the District webpage and our Facebook page. If you have not received links within 24 hours prior to your teacher’s meeting, please call the office.

post_text:
The Millville Area Elementary School will begin Technology distribution to students in Kindergarten, 1st and 2nd grades and their siblings on Friday, August 21st from 8:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m. and again from 4:00 p.m. to 6:00 p.m. through the Elementary Office entrance. When Kindergarten families come to pick up their technology supplies, we would like to provide an opportunity for students and families a tour of the building. We are prepared to show students and families most of the places students will go when they’re in school.
In an effort to be able to keep people appropriately socially distanced, please keep the number of family members to a minimum. We will attempt to socially distance families as much as possible and appreciate your compliance with wearing face coverings.

ATTENTION!! Parents of Seniors ATTENTION!!
Looking for a way to honor and recognize your Senior?
Creasy Signs can make a yard sign for you!
All you need to do is send one picture of your senior and the name of the student (as you want it to appear on the sign) to creasysigns@verizon.net. Missy is the contact person at Creasy Signs.
THE PICTURE AND NAME ARE DUE TO MISSY BY MAY 8th. Signs will be ready for pick up, at the high school on May 15th. Payment can be made when the sign is picked up.
The sign also includes the Millville logo and Class of 2020 and all information is printed on both sides.
Cost--$25 and this includes the yard stakes.
CONGRATULATIONS CLASS OF 2020!!

shared_text:
Millville Legion Canteen, Post 564
April 22 at 11:19 AM ·

We have some exciting news! We will be opening up this Tuesday, April 28th, for WINGS to go!

Seeing as we have not been open regularly, the full menu will not be available, just wings and sides.

You do have option of bone-in or boneless wings, but we will only be doing them by the dozen. Flavors are limited to the following: BBQ, Hooters, Garlic/Parm, Kickin' Bourbon, Mango/Habanero, and Mild. Celery and dressing available.

Sides available are: French fries, cheese curds, jalapeno cheese curds, and onion rings.

Orders will be taken from 4:45-8pm, or until supplies last.

**All proceeds from this evening will be donated to the Millville Area School District, to help provide families with meals during this time**

Also during this event, Millville Legion Aux will be collecting donations for the Millville Area School District. Specific items they are in need of/are having a hard time find are: cereal, p-nut butter, jelly/jam, ramen noodles, Beefaroni, ravioli. If you'd like to donate, we'd be happy to collect your items when we deliver your food. No need for you to get out.

Good morning! This is a message for the Juniors and Seniors about prom. In order to try to provide this special occasion that occurs at the end of the year, we have tentatively rescheduled the prom for Monday, August 3rd, from 5:00-9:00 PM at The Barn at Greenwood in Iola. We are looking into having it catered.
We are hopeful that the prom will be held, but it is a tentative plan and a final decision will be based on the large gathering guidelines we receive from the Governor for the month of August.
We are in this together! Take care!

post_text: Earlier today (April 9th, 2020), Governor Wolf and Secretary of Education Rivera closed PA schools through the end of the 2019-20 academic year, as defined by our local school calendar. This means we will be continuing with our virtual planned instruction. They closed the school buildings but did not discontinue the educational process. All students are expected to show a good faith effort in their classes/subjects by logging in, attending meetings, participating and completing assignments. The last student day for the 2019-20 school year is expected to be June 5, 2020.

Hemlock Township Police
March 25 at 4:18 PM ·

Stuck at home, bored & looking for something new?

Hemlock Township Police Dept is looking for the kids in our coverage area (Hemlock, Madison, Millville) to draw some new art work for our station.
There will be 3 winners.

Please submit all pictures by Wednesday April 1 at 8pm. The subject is up to the artist and can be painted, colored, sketched, etc. all pictures can be submitted by dropping it in the mail or emailing it to the township email located on our fb page and/or tag the picture on fb #HTPDChallenge1. Please make no smaller than 8x10 and no bigger than 12x15. On the picture please include your age, school, first name as well as phone number.

Winner will be announced Saturday April 4th at noon and we will possibly have another competition after so stay tuned.

Good Afternoon,
As the Athletic Director at Millville Area School District, here is an update on all spring athletics, including Junior High athletics.
In coordination with the PIAA District 4, and Mid-Penn athletic conferences, we will be suspending all athletics until April 1, 2020. This includes all open gyms, fundraisers, practices, and games.
As soon as more information is provided to me about the timeline for continuing spring athletics, I will pass it along.
I want to thank you for your cooperation during this time. Any question please feel free to contact me.

Mark Barnes
Athletic Director
Millville Area School District

post_text:
I wanted to inform Facebook followers that the Millville Elementary School did indeed, have an internal lockdown this morning for a short time. We discovered threatening messages on the office voicemail this morning. Police were immediately notified, the building was locked down, and an investigation was launched. The investigation resulted in the identification of the caller. As soon as the administration and police were positive that no threat existed, the lockdown was lifted. Privacy laws prevent further details from being shared, however I will share that at no time were students and staff in imminent danger. I appreciate the response from the Hemlock Township and Orangeville Area police departments and their assistance with this investigation. I also appreciate the response from faculty and staff to ensure the safety and welfare of our students.
Ed Sanders
Principal

Millville Area School District added 40 new photos — at Millville AreaElementarySchool.
February 13 at 2:21 PM · Millville, PA ·

Students at Millville Elementary have been busy the past few weeks raising money for the American Heart Association. The final total is not complete yet, but as of today, the students raised $6,349.94. This beats our total from last year. The winning class to register online was Mrs. Brandt's 4th grade class and the winning class collecting $1,352.05 was Mrs. Wolfe's class. First grader, Hillary Manning raised on her own, by running a mile for each donation, raised $500.43. Students then got to throw a pie at Mrs. Houseknecht and Mrs. Pell. Hillary and Mrs. Brandt got to slime our Superintendent, Mrs. Jenkins.

post_text: Chloe Abraczinskis Mehring, Aeronautical Engineer from NASA’s Johnson Space Center in Houston Texas, visited with students at the Millville Elementary School today. Chloe discussed the latest launch, history of NASA, and highlighted some careers in Space Science to students in grades K-6. Chloe is a 2003 graduate of Central Columbia and graduated from Penn State University. Students viewed mission videos from NASA as well as talked with Chloe about various careers available at NASA.

post_text: Millville Elementary Friends: Do you remember the two containers with box tops and money in them at the sign-in and sign-out sheet? Well, they are back with lots of Box Tops ready for "adoption". They are either expired, missing dates or codes and therefore, we can not exchange these for Box Top cash. Each box top is worth $ .10 and we are asking for your help in getting that money to our students for items at school. Would you be willing to "adopt" a box top? If you have extra change laying around feel free to drop it in the cup. We will collect the money and remove the expired box tops at the end of the each week. Thank you for your help! Also, don't forget to download the Box Top app and scan your receipt after each grocery store purchase. If you have a digital box top, it will be loaded in the Elementary School's account. The students, faculty and staff at Millville Elementary appreciate all of your efforts to help raise money for our students!!

post_text:
PRE-K Parents:
Today your students chose their first library book.

They are officially Millville Elementary library patrons. In pre-k, the students will choose books and keep their books in the classroom. This is the start of the practice of library book responsibility. This practice should be the basis for the responsibility of book care and book borrowing that they will do when they are kindergarten students. The students will have access to their library books in the classroom and will follow the same routine of book return that the older students use. However, the pressure is off because the students will not be bringing the books home. If you have any questions, do not hesitate to call the school and ask to speak with me. I am so excited to have your children in library class!

Thank you,
Librarian - Andrea Marquardt.
